<refentry id="MGR-MONITORGTM">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>MONITOR GTMCOOR</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>7</manvolnum>
    <refmiscinfo>Manage - Language Statements</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>MONITOR GTMCOOR</refname>
    <refpurpose>monitor the current state for gtmcoor in the ADB cluster</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <indexterm zone="mgr-monitorgtm">
    <primary>MONITOR GTMCOOR</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis>
MONITOR GTMCOOR [ ALL ]
MONITOR GTMCOOR { MASTER | SLAVE } [ ALL | <replaceable class="parameter">node_name</replaceable> ]
</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>
<command>MONITOR GTMCOOR</command> monitor the current state for gtmcoor in the ADB cluster node.
    </para>
    <para>
Node has three operating conditions: running, not running and reject connection.
    </para>

    <para>
    Running means is server is accepting connections.
    </para>

    <para>
    Not running means is could not establish connection.
    </para>

    <para>
    Reject connection means is server is alive but rejecting connections(e.g., recovery model or startup model).
    </para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <replaceable class="parameter">node_name</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
    Node name, corresponds to the name column in the node table.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>Examples</title>

    <para>
Monitor all gtmcoor:
<programlisting>
MONITOR GTMCOOR ALL;
</programlisting>
    </para>
  </refsect1>

      <refsect1>
    <title>See Also</title>

